; AlifePlus trade policy. Two stalker tiers split by RANK_VETERAN (12000, per ap_core_const).
; Entry order in each block = BUY priority (top entries fill first; cash exhausted = stop).
; Min/max counted in rounds for ammo categories (per xinventory D5), items otherwise.
; Sell-only categories use min=0, max=0 -- min=0 means count<0 never triggers buy.
; Pre-filter ("untouchable" + "equipped") bypasses policy entirely; never reached here.
; A row key is either a category (medkit, grenade, ...) or a single item section. An item uses
; its section's rule when that section is listed, otherwise its category's rule; an item that
; matches no row is left alone. Grenades are listed individually here so smoke (grenade_smoke)
; can be left out entirely -- trade never buys or sells it (engine crash on NPC throw). Smoke is
; purged from NPCs by the AlifeBalance cull, which names it. Ammo in rounds, items otherwise.

[ap_trade_policy_rookie]
ammo_slot_3_t1    = 15, 15
ammo_slot_2_t1    = 16, 16
ammo_slot_3_t2    = 0, 0
ammo_slot_2_t2    = 0, 0
ammo_not_equipped = 0, 0
